Asset backed trading is a type of trading where the value of the commodity is guaranteed by the underlying asset. In the case of a refiner, the asset is the crude oil or petroleum products that are being traded. Here are some ways a refiner can benefit from asset backed trading:

1. **Reduced risk**: Asset backed trading reduces the risk of default by the counterparty, as the value of the commodity is guaranteed by the underlying asset. This provides a higher level of security for the refiner.

* The access token is returned to the server-side, keeping it secure from client-side code.

You can use the following methods to inspect the UI in Xamarin.Forms:

#### 1. Visual Studio

*   Open your Xamarin.Forms project in Visual Studio.
*   Set a breakpoint in your code where you want to inspect the UI.
*   Run your app in debug mode.
*   When the breakpoint is hit, you can inspect the UI by using the Visual Studio debugger.

#### 2. Xamarin Inspector

*   Download and install the Xamarin Inspector from the Visual Studio Marketplace.
*   Open your Xamarin.Forms project in Visual Studio.
*   Run your app in debug mode.
*   Open the Xamarin Inspector by clicking on "View" > "Other Windows" > "Xamarin Inspector".
*   The Xamarin Inspector will display a list of all the UI elements in your app.

#### 3. Snoop

*   Download and install Snoop from the Visual Studio Marketplace.
*   Open your Xamarin.Forms project in Visual Studio.
*   Run your app in debug mode.
